Re: Warning : Check your system ( Help me )

Bitcointalk

2010-09-23 16:28:25 UTC - [11]Original Post

   I donʼt understand, are you under the impression that the program sets
   the system clock?  It doesnʼt.
   [12]Quote from: Cdecker on September 19, 2010, 08:14:08 PM
   We already have ways to synchronize (approximately) the clients, so why
   not make use of that?
   We use an internal offset based on the median of other nodesʼ times,
   but for security reasons we donʼt let them offset us by more than an
   hour.  If they indicate weʼre off by more than an hour, then we resort
   to alerting the user to fix their clock.
